    <chapter xml:id="F_A_Q">
        <title>Frequently asked questions</title>
        <para><emphasis role="bold">Q:</emphasis> Why did the DevDoc
            writers write these recipes? </para>
        <para><emphasis role="bold">A:</emphasis> Writers like to
            write. Writers like to eat. 
            Writers like to write about
            things to eat.
            Writers like to read about
            things to eat. 
            It's all good.</para>
        <para><emphasis role="bold">Q:</emphasis> Did the DevDoc
            writers invent these recipes? </para>
        <para><emphasis role="bold">A:</emphasis> Probably not. We're
            <emphasis role="italic">technical</emphasis> writers.
            That means we spend most of our time explaining things
            that other people invented. We like inventions. We like
            writing about inventions almost as much as we like writing
            about things to eat. We can't eat most of the inventions 
            that we write about, but we might try to eat some of these.
        </para>
        <para><emphasis role="bold">Q:</emphasis> Are these the only recipes the DevDoc
            writers know? </para>
        <para><emphasis role="bold">A:</emphasis> Hardly. 
            We always
            know much more than we tell. 
            We like these recipes and we're happy to share them.
            In a future release, especially 
            after analyzing reader feedback and 
            recruiting additional contributors,
            we may share more.
        </para>
        <para><emphasis role="bold">Q:</emphasis> Did the DevDoc
            writers test these recipes? </para>
        <para><emphasis role="bold">A:</emphasis> Let's just say that
            some of us have tried some of the recipes, from our source
            material but not from this document, so it's always
            possible that something was lost in the transition to this
            format. We mean well, but we don't have any QE resources.
            You should make a small batch and taste it before trying
            to impress your customers with anything you find in this
            starter kit.</para>
    </chapter>
